Overview.Summary:
The 2020 Greek presidential election took place on January 22, 2020 (1,2). Katerina Sakellaropoulou was elected as the 13th and first female President of Greece (2). The election was an indirect one, with the incumbent President Prokopis Pavlopoulos not being suggested for reelection (1). In the US, Kamala Harris ended her 2020 presidential campaign on December 4, 2019 (3). Income inequality was a major issue for 2020 candidates, with universal basic income being proposed as a solution (5). In Africa, previous presidential elections involved a system of thousands of clan delegates voting for parliamentary representatives who then elected the President (6). There have been predictions made about the outcome of the 2020 US presidential election (7,8). In the US, there have been discussions about potentially serving only one term if elected president (9). In Taiwan, a presidential election took place on January 11, 2020 (10). Michael Bennet dropped out of the 2020 presidential race on February 11, 2020 (11). In Las Vegas, a Democratic primary presidential debate took place on February 19, 2020 (12). In Spain, Javier Tebas was re-elected as LaLiga president on December 23, 2019 (13). In the UK, the 2019 General Election took place on December 12, 2019 (14). There have been various other elections taking place globally, including in Algeria and Namibia (16,17). The US uses an electoral college system for presidential elections (18). Elizabeth Warren ended her 2020 run on March 5, 2020 (19). High turnout was reported in many areas during the election (20).
